TIPS FOR EFFECTIVE NETWORKING EMAILS
=============================================================================

1. PERSONALIZE EACH MESSAGE
   • Research the recipient before reaching out
   • Reference specific aspects of their work or background
   • Explain why you're contacting them specifically

2. BE CLEAR AND CONCISE
   • State your purpose early in the email
   • Respect their time with brevity
   • Use short paragraphs for readability

3. PROVIDE VALUE
   • Offer something helpful when possible
   • Share relevant content or opportunities
   • Express genuine appreciation for their work

4. FOLLOW EMAIL ETIQUETTE
   • Use a professional email address
   • Create a clear, specific subject line
   • Proofread carefully before sending

5. FOLLOW UP APPROPRIATELY
   • Wait at least one week before following up
   • Be polite and understanding if you don't receive a response
   • Limit follow-ups to 1-2 messages

6. BUILD RELATIONSHIPS, NOT TRANSACTIONS
   • Focus on establishing a genuine connection
   • Show interest in their expertise, not just what they can do for you
   • Maintain the relationship with occasional check-ins

7. EXPRESS GRATITUDE
   • Always thank contacts for their time and assistance
   • Be specific about how they've helped you
   • Offer to reciprocate when possible 